column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Moderate Wind
column13: Control is channel and appears clear. Ice still on lake with exception of ~6m of open shoreline.
column14: Wading (conventional price meter - low SNR), ~50m d/s lake outlet. Ice still on lake with ~6m open along shoreline. Large visible sandbar just outside mouth of river, spans more than width of river. Ice is ~100m from outlet of river. New curve to be developed for this station (unable to access current curve for some reason). Measurement does not currenlty plot on curve however within scatter of previous measurements. Previous two measurements (Feb & March) plotted well to left also. Explored outlet sill (soft mobile, sandy bottom), maximum depth is 0.44m therefore 0 flow offset could be 1.728m (2.168m-0.44m). Could be higher but shouldn't be lower than this value. HFC Comments: Control Condition: CLERMeasurement Section Codition: OPENWeather Condition: clerWind Velocity: 20-30Wind Direction: S DWL taken at 08AA007. See notes for station visit. Logger value (AQ) used for post measurement stage value.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind Swirling/Variable
column13: 95% open water but some ice shelves that are likely impacting the chanel shape and Stage-Q relationship.
column14: To RFT: Curve data not working for this eHSN, rating curve was expecting 2.4cms today but had similar stage and discharge to Feb 2024 measurement. Please don't shift to this measurement, we will decide what to do with these results in office. Low quality measurement, strong winds upstream, downstream, and across stream. While watching the cups on the price meter it is obvious the affect the wind has on velocity at this site from panel to panel. Depths were noted to appear 4cm higher or lower on wading rod depending on what wind was doing. Ice panels flowing through measurement section, multiple times a tidal wave like effect surged d/s during measurement.  KW has photo of HFC cross section summary will upload at later date. -levels from Sekulmun Lake station 08AA007 which was visited imediately before the river site. Only one water level as the logger at 08AA007 was going through an OS update and we didn't have time/fuel to fly back to the lake station. This isn't ideal for MGH as station does bounce around, however it was a ice and wind affected measurement that won't be helpful in aiding future rating development. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Moderate Wind Swirling/Variable
column13:
~0.25m of shore ice at wading section.
- 1 to 3m ice of either bank u/s and d/s from wading section.
-complete ice cover on lake ~50m u/s, although ice in this area was deteriorating during mmt and large ice pans were floating down during measurement.
-complete ice cover ~500m d/s of measruement section.
column14: -Double checked Wade's depths, did a rough spin test (difficult in the wind), price meter was fresh from callibration, we had checked callibration parameters were accurate by calculating velocity by counting beeps in office prior to trip, no vegetation affecting measurement, edges were accurate. High quality measurement, so decided not to remeasure and trust this measurement over the curve due to easy changes to base rating that could be affected by strong winds blowing sand into channel, possibility of ice causing backwater, and strong winds during measurement ranging from ~10km/hour to 35km/hour switching back and forth from u/s to d/s during measurement. Control Condition: CLERMeasurement Section Codition: OPENWeather Condition: clerWind Velocity: 10KMWind Direction: S Logger values come from 08AA007 Sekulmun Lake where survey was completed with helicopter pilot (Matt), Kyle checked the DWL cut Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column14: - ~20km/hour winds blowing downstream during mmt. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ -no stage sensor, use stage logger values from lake station 08AA007 to calculate MGH. -used the DWL from 08AA007 for preliminary rating curve error. -applied -0.002m SRC to MGH as noted at 10:05 DWL. Mid-section
GC: 0.000 DWL

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Control is lake outlet/channel & appears clear.
column14: Wading (FT2) measurement 50m D/S of mouth (at constriction). Panels: 23. Mean SNR: 10.5dB. Max. (q/Q): 5.6%. Uncertainty (ISO): 2.6%. No Quality Control warnings (low SNR warnings but did not exceed threshold). High confidence measurement.  @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Stage values used for measurement mean gauge heights are from 08AA007 - SEKULMUN LAKE NEAR WHITEHORSE which is ~4km away on the western shore of the lake. 08AA007 was visited first to allow assessment of the Rating Error obtained at 08AA008.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: Lake outlet 98% open, Small amount of ice on edges of outlet flow, and some ice mid channel in outlet - probably causing slight BW.
column14: Wading mmnt made at normal location. ~.5m of thin ice overhanging channel on each side of wading section. eHSN will not attach summary file for some reason. Copies of summary file are in the mmnt folder. Stage data from 08AA007, See note from 08AA007 for surveying information. Gauge was reset prior to mmnt time so no SRC is needed for MGH. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column14: Waded at outlet, 10m downstream of mouth. Laminar flow conditions, and steady deep water. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Stage values used from Sekulmun Lake gauge, as well as SRC from DWL taken at lake gauge.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column14: Calm conditions on Sekulmun Lake durring mmnt. No side channel flow. Channel too deep to do wading mmnt at lake outlet, used SP with RC boat. Stage data and SRC for MGH from 08AA007. ADCP by Moving Boat

column13: Lake Outlet almost completely frozen over
column14: Under ice mmnt. CIC on river, lake outlet almost completely frozen, with only a couple small open areas. No visit to 08AA007 gauge due to extreme winds on Lake - winds up to 80km/hr. Ice affected mmnt so accuracy of MGH less important. MGH based on gauge readings with no SRC Mid-section

column13: Outflow of lake starting to ice over. 1-4m ice on edges, with ~8-10m wide open channel.
column14: Mixed mmnt with ice on edges and open water conditions in centre. Levels from Lake gauge Mid-section
